Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the chunks onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, sprinkle over the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, then toss to coat.

Spread out in a single layer. TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary. When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

In the meantime, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In a large #bowl{}, add the @British chicken breasts{2}, garlic, @lemon & herb seasoning{2%tsp} and a good drizzle of @olive oil{}.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the pan is hot, lay the chicken flat in the pan.

Fry until browned all over, ~{5%minutes} each side.

Once the chicken is browned, pop it onto a #baking tray{} lined with #foil{}.

Bake on the middle shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, wipe out the pan used for the chicken breasts.

When the potatoes have 5 mins remaining return the now empty chicken pan to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Transfer the peas to a bowl and leave to one side. Cover with a #lid{} or foil to keep warm.

Return the now empty pan to a medium-high heat and add the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @fresh pesto{32%g} and @water{75%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for amount). Stir to combine, bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add a splash of water if a little too thick.

When everything's ready, share the chicken between your #serving plates{}. Serve the roasted potatoes and peas alongside.

Finish by spooning the creamy pesto sauce over your chicken. Enjoy!